==English==
==={{initialism}}===
'''OMG'''

#(''Internet slang'') [[Oh my God]]; variants include OMFG, and ZOMG,  ''Zo Oh My God'', [[OMC]], ETC.
# (''Computing'') the Object Management Group (who define [[CORBA]])
#(''Military formation'') [[Operational Manoeuvre Group Eng.; Оперативная Группа Маневра Rus.,]]; A formation in size larger then a division and smaller then an army, first used by the Red Army during WW2 as a Cavalry-Mechanised Group [[конно-механизированная группа КМГ]]. The purpose of the OMG is to exploit penetrations of enemy defences, and inflict damage to enemy rear areas. The OMG can be based on a single Corps level headquarters, or a number of smaller units detached for a particular operation.
